CatDescriptText: Lynn Morrow, airlines agent, Sheridan and Homer Antonette, state employe[e], Shadyside were part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper, January 23, 1960, pg. A1 with question "Do you believe the people who vote only for the President every four years make the best citizens?"  Mr. Morrow's answer reads: "They are not very good citizens...You should vote every election.  It's a duty and right..."  Mr. Antonette's answer reads "They are not the most ideal...If they don't take care of things on a lower scale, our vote becomes diluted."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Lynn Morrow wearing eyeglasses, plaid shirt, and dark zippered jacket with plaid lining, standing in front of building, Downtown; Portrait of Homer Antonette wearing fedora with dark band and diagonally striped tie, standing in front of building, Downtown
